stickerText: Joe Biden’s Presidential election comes 48 years to the day he was 1st elected to Senate on Nov. 7 1972.
About a month later, his wife & daughter were killed in an accident. His sons Beau & Hunter were hospitalized.
Biden considered resigning, but the Senate Dem leader convinced him not to.
He was sworn in at Beau’s bedside in the hospital 🥺.
Beau Biden died from brain cancer in 2015.
In 2016, Biden opted not to run for President, following the grief of Beau’s death.

“...with my family, and I want to help change the country and the world for the better.” - Joe Biden
